
# Introduction ðŸ¤´âš”

This is a fully automated solution ðŸ¤–ðŸ§ž that allows you to deploy an NFT with a single API call to the [Polygon Matic](https://polygon.technology/) blockchain ( this is a layer 2 Ethereum network). Other blockchains will be added in the future ( BSC, CELO, ONE).

## Key points ðŸ¥‡ðŸ”‘

- Jobs are placed in a resilient Redis queue.

- Deploy a smart contract for each collection

- Uploads base64 data to [IPFS](https://ipfs.io/) (The InterPlanetary File System)

- Create the NFT Json Metadata and include the [IPFS](https://ipfs.io/)  results in it, as specified by your custom path. (Internally is done by [lodash _.set](https://lodash.com/docs/4.17.15#set))

- Upload the compiled NFT Json Metadata to [IPFS](https://ipfs.io/) 

- Deploy the NFT to the blockchain

- Use a webhook to notify you of the stages and status of the job.

### Why use a job queue ðŸ¤”â›‘
Because of the nature of these networks and technology; There are multiple failure points related to network congestion, timeouts, incompletion, or erroneous results either on Blockchain or the [IPFS](https://ipfs.io/). That is why we set up a resilience work queue, which attempts each step until the NFT is successfully deployed. To ensure that the NFT is deployed, jobs are retried 10 times until the error status is marked as unrecoverable.
